HEADWORD: Zachun
<hw>Za*chun"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>An oil pressed by the Arabs from the fruit of a small thorny tree
(<spn>Balanites Aegyptiaca</spn>), and sold to pilgrims for a healing
ointment.</def> <rj><au>J. Smith (Dict. Econ. Plants).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

